The LM ascent stage was jettisoned at 1972-04-24T20:54:12 UST. It had been targeted to impact near the Apollo 16 site; however, this impact was not possible because of a loss of attitude control, Tire estimated orbital life of the LM ascent stage is about 1 yr. Apollo 16 - Preliminary Science Report, 1972.

Data provided at https://history.nasa.gov/SP-4029/Apollo_18-29_LM_Lunar_Impact.htm were compiled from the mission report for each flight. Times are when signals received on Earth. Actual landing site coordinates based on International Astronomical Union (IAU) Mean Earth Polar Axis coordinate system as described in the Journal of  Geophysical Research, vol. 105, pages 20,227 to 20,280, 2000.
